<DOC><DOCNO> AP881123-0267 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-11-23-88 1112EST</FILEID><FIRST>r f PM-USSprint     11-23 0146</FIRST><SECOND>PM-US Sprint,0150</SECOND><HEAD>Announces New System to Speed Call Transmissions</HEAD><DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   US Sprint Communications Co. said today it hasdeployed a system of signal enhancements that will speed voice anddata transmissions through its fiber optic network.   The system will improve call set-up time to put calls through anaverage of three seconds faster and improve the company's automatedvalidation system to increase its ability to detect toll fraud, USSprint said.   The company said the signaling system is critical to its plans toprovide future features and functions of its network. Earlier thismonth, US Sprint completed the final segment of its third plannedtranscontinental fiber route, so that all calls over its network nowgo over fiber.   US Sprint, a partnership of United Telecommunicationis Inc. ofKansas City and GTE Corp. of Stamford, Conn., is the nation'sthird-largest long-distance telephone company.</TEXT></DOC>